{"id":43851,"date":"2025-07-03T13:16:58","date_gmt":"2025-07-03T09:16:58","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=43851"},"modified":"2025-07-03T13:16:58","modified_gmt":"2025-07-03T09:16:58","slug":"ahmad-cursing-makruh","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2025\/07\/03\/ahmad-cursing-makruh\/","title":{"rendered":"Ahmad on Curses: Disapproval of praying against people by name"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Salih reported: A man mentioned Al-Hajjaj or others to his father, Ahmad ibn Hanbal, may Allah be pleased with him, saying, \u201cLet him be cursed!\u201d Ahmad said, \u201cI do not like for it to be uttered.\u201d Then, Ahmad said, \u201c<strong>Surely, the curse of Allah is upon the wrongdoers.<\/strong>\u201d (11:18)<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Sunnah li-Abi\u0304 Bakr al-Khalla\u0304l 851<\/p>\n<p>Shaykh al-Islam Ibn Taymiyyah commented, \u201cAhmad is known to have disapproved of cursing specific people by name, such as Al-Hajjaj ibn Yusuf and their likes, but rather he would say as Allah Almighty said: <strong>Surely, the curse of Allah is upon the wrongdoers.<\/strong>\u201d (11:18)<\/p>\n<p>Source: Minha\u0304j al-Sunnah 4\/569<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0635\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0650\u062d\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0644\u0650\u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0647\u0650 \u064a\u0639\u0646\u064a \u0623\u064e\u062d\u0652\u0645\u064e\u062f \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u062d\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0644\u064d \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0631\u064e\u0651\u062c\u064f\u0644\u064f \u064a\u064f\u0630\u0652\u0643\u064e\u0631\u064f \u0639\u0650\u0646\u0652\u062f\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062d\u064e\u062c\u064e\u0651\u0627\u062c\u064f \u0623\u064e\u0648\u0652 \u063a\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064f\u0647\u064f \u0641\u064e\u064a\u064